<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Geez Riffi, your right, we are all clerics...And many times its been said that this quest was flawed in the fact that in order to do it in a timely fashion, you have to keep the PH alive. Its not like we want it that way. But many of us would like the Aegis of Life, because 1)it is a great piece of equipment ac-wise 2)its a good piece of equipment for wis. 

I also actually enjoy doing the few cleric-centric quests that there are in the game, so trying to complete this quest (once I am able to) will give me a sense of accomplishment, knowing that I vanquished the evil grimrot in order to complete the quest, and was rewarded with the Aegis for my effort...Sortof like the feeling I recently got when I killed Dwigus and Sludge, for my breastplate, and finished off the Paw of Opalla quest...Is it wrong to want a cool item for my character? I don't think so...

you're a cleric...would you REALLY screw up the spawn at that camp for another cleric or paladin who was trying to finish that quest? If so, that is just sad...If you don't want the shield, for whatever reason, don't take your anger out on fellow clerics that do..

